    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "sp_cmdshell_run_test",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to enable and execute the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "xp_cmdshell",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " extended stored procedure in Microsoft SQL Server. This procedure first configures the server to allow advanced options, then enables the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "xp_cmdshell",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " feature, and finally executes a command to list the contents of the root directory of the C: drive using the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "DIR",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " command."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity level of this stored procedure is low. It involves straightforward configuration changes and a single command execution. The logic is linear and does not involve any conditional branching or complex operations."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "This stored procedure does not take any input parameters. It is designed to execute a predefined set of operations without any external input."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "4. Business Logic and Workflow"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "SET NOCOUNT ON",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": This command is used to prevent the SQL Server from sending messages about the number of rows affected by T-SQL statements. This is generally used to reduce unnecessary network traffic."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Enable Advanced Options",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure uses "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "sp_configure",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " to enable 'show advanced options', which allows the configuration of advanced server options."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Enable xp_cmdshell",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure then enables the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "xp_cmdshell",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " feature, which allows the execution of shell commands directly from SQL Server."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Execute Shell Command",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": Finally, the procedure executes the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "xp_cmdshell",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " command to list all files and directories in the root of the C: drive."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "5. Performance Considerations"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Minimal Performance Impact",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure itself does not perform any resource-intensive operations. However, enabling "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "xp_cmdshell",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " can have performance implications if used to execute resource-heavy shell commands."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Network Traffic",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The use of "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "SET NOCOUNT ON",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " helps in reducing unnecessary network traffic by suppressing row count messages."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "6. Potential Issues or Risks"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Security Risks",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": Enabling "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "xp_cmdshell",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " poses significant security risks as it allows execution of arbitrary shell commands, which can be exploited by malicious users to execute harmful commands on the server."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Permission Requirements",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": Only users with appropriate permissions can enable "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "xp_cmdshell",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ". This procedure should be executed with caution and typically requires sysadmin privileges."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Audit and Compliance",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": Enabling "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "xp_cmdshell",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " might violate security policies or compliance requirements in certain environments. It is crucial to ensure that its usage is justified and monitored."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Error Handling",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": The procedure lacks error handling mechanisms. If any of the commands fail, the procedure will not provide feedback or handle the error gracefully."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Overall, while the procedure is simple, it involves enabling a powerful feature that should be managed carefully due to its potential security implications."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "7. Stored Procedure Definition"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "codeBlock",
      "attrs": {
        "language": "sql"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "-- =============================================\n-- Author:\t\t<Author,,Name>\r\n-- Create date: <Create Date,,>\r\n-- Description:\t<Description,,>\r\n-- =============================================\r\nCREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[sp_cmdshell_run_test] \r\n\r\nAS\r\nBEGIN\r\n\t-- SET NOCOUNT ON added to prevent extra result sets from\r\n\t-- interfering with SELECT statements.\r\n\tSET NOCOUNT ON;\r\n\r\n    -- Insert statements for procedure here\r\n\tEXEC sp_configure 'show advanced options', 1\r\nRECONFIGURE\r\nEXEC sp_configure 'xp_cmdshell', 1\r\nRECONFIGURE\r\nEXEC xp_cmdshell 'DIR C:\\*.*'\r\nEND"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
